<font color="#FF0000">NO GUILT</font><br>
<tt>Fri May  2  1:41:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was born into a John Wayne society that meant God and Country so on my 18th birthday in Dec 1972 I enlisted in the Navy I tried to volenteer for VietNam but I was told that they weren't sending anymore troops. So I felt cheated. I could not bring myself to say I was an era vet, but damnit I was ready to go I wore the uniform, guys were still dying and I couldn't do a damn thing about it until my first visit to the wall and I made my peace with the 58,000 and myself.  <br>
 If you wore the uniform from 1962 to 1975 you were part of it no matter what your role you were there so be proud what you did. Just because you didn't throw the ball or make the big play you were still part of the team avalible to do your duty to God &amp; Country.<br>

